      "body_md": "Audit Tool **1.0.3** — full artifact set (server + agents).\n\n### Server (main tool)\n- `audit-tool_1.0.3_amd64.deb` · `audit-tool-1.0.3-1.x86_64.rpm` (self-contained: bundled python3.12 wheelhouse, systemd unit, customer-docs)\n- In-place update bundles: `audit-toolkit-1.0.3-application.tar.gz`, `-audits.tar.gz`\n\n### Agents (fleet / standalone / hypervisor)\n- **deb**: `fleet-agent_1.0.3_amd64.deb` · `standalone-agent_1.0.3_amd64.deb` · `hypervisor-agent_1.0.3_amd64.deb`\n- **rpm**: `*-1.0.3-1.x86_64.rpm` (all three)\n- **msi** (Windows, embedded python): `audit-fleet-agent` · `audit-standalone-agent` · `audittoolkit-hypervisor-agent` `-1.0.3-windows-x64.msi`\n\n`SHA256SUMS-1.0.3.txt` covers every asset.\n\n### Signing note\nThis is a full, working release — every artifact installs and runs normally. The only caveat: the Windows MSIs are **self-signed** (a self-signed AuditToolkit certificate, not Azure Trusted Signing / a publicly-trusted CA), so Windows shows an \"unknown publisher\" warning during install. The installers are otherwise complete and fully functional. Moving MSI signing to Azure Trusted Signing is a planned future improvement, not a release blocker.\n",
